      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Identify the reagents <b>a</b>–<b>e</b> in the following scheme:</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBcmtYIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--695662cd8c081289f8cb2b773a66ecaebb284a21/OChem_18_EC_048.jpg\" alt=\"Cyclohexanone is transformed into 1-methylcyclohexanol by reagent a; b and c convert 1-methylcyclohexanol to 1-methylcyclohexene and 1-methyl-1-methoxycyclohexane respectively. D converts 1-methylcyclohexene into 1,2-epoxy-1-methylcyclohexane, which is converted by e into (1S,2S)-1-methylcyclohexan-1,2-diol. \">",
